attributes.Transcription: We'll now operate the Nintendo Switch.

attributes.Long form description: The student changes the handheld controller mode to the JoyCon comfort grip, inspects the console presses the button on the back of each controller, detaches them off the console, and attaches them to the JoyCon comfort grip.  Then, the student changes the controller JoyCon comfort grip to two JoyCons. Detach each controller from de JoyCon comfort grip and attaches the JoyCon straps. He changes the two JoyCons controller back to the Handheld mode by detaching the  JoyCon straps and attaching the JoyCon controllers to the Nintendo Switch.  After that, he stands the Nintendo using the kickstand in the back of the console.  The instructor asks the student to change the game card of the Nintendo Switch. Closes the Kickstand, opens the SD card lid, pulls the old SD card, and changes it for the new one.  The student turns on the Nintendo Switch by pressing the power button and turns off the Nintendo Switch by pressing the button for three seconds, clicking on the touch screen, and turning off the console.
